  <p>
    Chat screenshots sell. A conversation feels more real than a paragraph of copy — it's why product pages, pitch decks, app-store listings and onboarding flows are full of them. But you can't always screenshot a real chat: the feature isn't built yet, real messages contain private data, or you need a clean example that shows the exact flow. So teams mock them up. Done right, that's completely legitimate. Done carelessly, it crosses into misleading your audience.
  </p>

  <p>
    This guide covers where fake chat screenshots are fair game, where they aren't, and how to use them so your demos stay honest — plus a free, no-watermark tool to make them.
  </p>

